In [25]:
def get_num_season(x):
    #print(x)
    y=str(x).strip()
    #print(y)
    if 'Season' in y:
        y1=y.split()[0]
        #print(y1)
        y2=int(y1)
        #print(y2)
    else:
        y2=-1
    return y2
In [26]:
def get_duration_mins(x):
    y=str(x).strip()
    if 'min' in y:
        y1=y.split()[0]
        y2=int(y1)
    else:
        y2=-1
    return y2
In [27]:
df['duration_min'] = df['duration'].apply(get_duration_mins)
In [28]:
df['num_season'] = df['duration'].apply(get_num_season)

Top 20 Director Counts¶

In [40]:
top_val = 20
df1 = df.query('director != ""')\
        .groupby('director')\
        .size()\
        .reset_index()\
        .rename(columns={0:'director_count'})\
        .sort_values('director_count', ascending=False)\
        .head(top_val)

ax = df1.plot(
    kind='bar', 
    x='director',
    y='director_count',
    figsize=(12, 5),
    title=f'Top {top_val} Director Counts',
    color="#FFDAB9")

ax.set_facecolor("#F5F5F5")
ax.set_xlabel('Director Counts')
plt.show()

def add_labels(ax,df):
    x = df.index
    y = df.values
    pdn = df.values.max() * 0.02
    for i in range(len(x)):
        ax.text(i , 
                y[i]+pdn,
                str(y[i]), 
                ha = 'center', 
                bbox = dict(facecolor = 'yellow', alpha = 0.5)
            )
        ax.set_ylim(0, df.values.max() * 1.1)
        ax.set_xticklabels(x, rotation = 45, ha = 'right')
